Sentencas: Multi-element-doped BaBi0.05Zr0.1Co0.85-xNbxO3-delta(x = 0 or 0.05, and denoted as BBZC, BBZCN, respectively) perovskite oxides are fabricated and the phase composition, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion, and electrochemical performance are investigated.
Titulo: Comparative studies of BaBi0.05Zr0.1Co0.85-xNbxO3-δ(x=0 and 0.05) as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With 5% Nb substitution, BBZCN exhibits improved phase structure and a reduced thermal expansion coefficient.
Titulo: Comparative studies of BaBi0.05Zr0.1Co0.85-xNbxO3-δ(x=0 and 0.05) as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The BBZC and BBZCN cathodes exhibited chemical compatibility with the La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta(LSGM) electrolyte.
Titulo: Comparative studies of BaBi0.05Zr0.1Co0.85-xNbxO3-δ(x=0 and 0.05) as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area-specific resistances of the BBZC and BBZCN cathodes are 0.021 and 0.023 ohm cm(2)with LSGM electrolyte at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Comparative studies of BaBi0.05Zr0.1Co0.85-xNbxO3-δ(x=0 and 0.05) as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The peak power densities of 515 and 566 mW cm(-2)are obtained from single cell with BBZC and BBZCN cathodes at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Comparative studies of BaBi0.05Zr0.1Co0.85-xNbxO3-δ(x=0 and 0.05) as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that BBZC and BBZCN perovskite oxides will be a promising candidate as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Comparative studies of BaBi0.05Zr0.1Co0.85-xNbxO3-δ(x=0 and 0.05) as cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
